Develop friendships with the Townsfolk by giving them items. Your friendship level with each will increase faster depending on the items you give them, but be careful because certain items will damage your friendship as well.

[item]See [url=https://buddy.farm/townsfolk/]https://buddy.farm/townsfolk/[/url] or [[Gifts]] for what to give to the townsfolk[/item][item]The max friendship level that you can have is 99. You need the same amount of XP to reach that as you would for a skill. 2 billion XP for lvl 99. See [[Level XP]] for a chart[/item][item][b]Loved[/b] items give 150 XP while [b]Liked Items[/b] give 25 XP.[/item][item][b]Hated[/b] items give -50 XP.[/item][item]You also get a small amount of XP by competing help requests[/item][item]You can give as many items as you want, there is no limit[/item][item]There is a 'Townsfolk of the Day'. Each day a Townsfolk will be selected at random and all items given to that Townsfolk will give 2x XP towards Friendship. The same person cannot be chosen 2 days in a row.[/item][item]You get items from townsfolk every 10 levels, similar to level up rewards, including recipes that are vital for [[Cooking]]
